1
00:00:05,333 --> 00:00:07,433
I'm not Heo Dong Jin.

2
00:00:58,867 --> 00:01:00,633
Dad!

3
00:01:02,067 --> 00:01:03,367
No!

4
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:04,567
Dad!

5
00:01:04,567 --> 00:01:05,567
Tae Jeong, come out!

6
00:01:05,567 --> 00:01:08,000
No! It's dangerous!

7
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Sir, please help save my dad.

8
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:14,767
We found the body of a 40-year-old male
inside a car at Dongcheon Reservoir.

9
00:01:14,767 --> 00:01:17,000
Immediate support requested at the scene.

10
00:02:48,367 --> 00:02:50,333
Don't go.

11
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:53,367
Please.

12
00:04:58,867 --> 00:05:02,967
What should I do? I must have lost my mind.

13
00:06:09,267 --> 00:06:12,500
Are you feeling okay?

14
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:15,233
Yes, I'm fine.

15
00:06:15,900 --> 00:06:18,267
Thank you for yesterday.

16
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:31,700
So what was all that about?

17
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,767
It was during a heavy rainstorm

18
00:06:33,767 --> 00:06:36,867
that my dad's body
was found in the reservoir.

19
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:42,033
Ever since then, every time it rains heavily,

20
00:06:42,033 --> 00:06:44,833
I sometimes feel overwhelmed.

21
00:06:44,833 --> 00:06:48,733
By the way, can you answer
what I asked you yesterday?

22
00:06:51,133 --> 00:06:53,367
Why did you come to this house?

23
00:06:53,367 --> 00:06:56,800
I want you to be honest with me.

24
00:07:00,067 --> 00:07:03,933
Proof. I came to find proof.

25
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:05,967
Proof?

26
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:11,167
Ever since my brother
left home to meet Heo Dong Hwa,

27
00:07:11,167 --> 00:07:13,033
he never came back.

28
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,800
What?

29
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,800
My brother lent Heo Dong Hwa
a large sum of money.

30
00:07:20,933 --> 00:07:24,267
Then you should have
reported it to the police.

31
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:26,167
Why did you come here yourself?

32
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:28,767
How do I know you're not lying right now?

33
00:07:28,767 --> 00:07:31,300
I did try to report it.

34
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:34,667
But they just said
that most cases like this are simply runaways

35
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:36,100
and told me to wait for him.

36
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:40,567
So you broke in
and pretended to be a family member?

37
00:07:46,267 --> 00:07:51,167
I think Heo Dong Hwa
is involved in my brother's disappearance.

38
00:07:53,967 --> 00:07:58,933
Dong Hwa wouldn't do something that bad.

39
00:07:58,933 --> 00:08:01,067
Just because you knew him a certain way

40
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:04,867
doesn't mean that's all there was to him.

41
00:08:14,500 --> 00:08:18,300
What? Why are you here?
Didn't you say you left?

42
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,133
Kang Chul Jin?

43
00:08:22,333 --> 00:08:25,533
I guess Dong Hwa came back, huh?

44
00:08:25,533 --> 00:08:27,433
Not really.

45
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,600
But I got a message.

46
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:35,400
[Tae Jeong, I just saw your text
because I'm abroad.]

47
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:41,133
Tae Jeong, I just saw your text
because I'm abroad.

48
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:45,033
I don't think it's a good idea
that you stay at my house, sorry.

49
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:49,467
Abroad?

50
00:08:52,767 --> 00:08:55,800
By the way, what are you doing here so early?

51
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:59,867
I was worried about Dong Hwa.
Am I not allowed to come?

52
00:08:59,867 --> 00:09:02,000
Didn't Dong Hwa call you?

53
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:05,433
Nope, I haven't heard a thing.

54
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:08,433
Ah, by the way,

55
00:09:08,433 --> 00:09:11,667
you said you were here with Dong Jin, right?

56
00:09:11,667 --> 00:09:13,933
Tell me more about that.

57
00:09:15,433 --> 00:09:17,200
- Why?
- Why else, you idiot?

58
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,733
Gotta catch the impersonator.

59
00:09:18,733 --> 00:09:20,667
You didn't believe me.

60
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:22,800
At the time I didn't,

61
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:26,767
but I've thought about it,
and you have no reason to lie to me.

62
00:09:26,767 --> 00:09:31,033
Plus, I found out this idiot Dong Hwa
had money problems.

63
00:09:31,033 --> 00:09:33,133
So maybe someone holding a grudge

64
00:09:33,133 --> 00:09:36,933
impersonated his family or something.

65
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:39,700
Anyway, that weirdo isn't here now.

66
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:43,000
Tell me. What did he look like?

67
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,133
Actually, there was no one.

68
00:09:47,133 --> 00:09:51,200
Ah, darn it! What kind of crap is this?

69
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:53,500
Are you saying you lied?

70
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,467
Yeah, man.

71
00:09:57,067 --> 00:09:58,767
Seriously?

72
00:10:00,467 --> 00:10:04,433
I just wanted to mess with you,
since I haven't seen you in a while.

73
00:10:08,967 --> 00:10:11,133
Can I come in?

74
00:10:14,733 --> 00:10:16,633
Why do you want to go inside?

75
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:20,033
Well, what if something happened to Dong Hwa?

76
00:10:20,033 --> 00:10:22,300
I gotta take a look.

77
00:10:24,033 --> 00:10:26,867
He texted me, though.

78
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:31,300
Then why hasn't this punk reached out to me?

79
00:10:31,300 --> 00:10:33,700
Show me that text.

80
00:10:42,833 --> 00:10:44,833
I don't have my phone on me.

81
00:10:44,833 --> 00:10:48,400
Good, you can show it to me inside.

82
00:10:51,867 --> 00:10:54,500
Where are you, Heo Dong Hwa?

83
00:10:56,200 --> 00:10:59,367
Bet this punk's passed out again somewhere.

84
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:07,033
How long has he not come home?

85
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:11,333
Last time we texted was 4 or 5 days ago.

86
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:15,867
Ah, look at this fancy stuff.

87
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:18,400
Did you buy this?

88
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,967
Huh? Yeah.

89
00:11:19,967 --> 00:11:22,267
Were you planning to eat all this yourself?

90
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:26,300
Are you on a staycation or what?

91
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:39,967
Why are you trying to check the bedroom?

92
00:11:39,967 --> 00:11:41,767
Get out of my way.

93
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,267
No one's really here.

94
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:57,633
I told you, it was a joke.

95
00:12:29,033 --> 00:12:32,433
Not here either. Come on, this is so lame.

96
00:12:32,433 --> 00:12:35,733
Thought you were hiding
a secret lover or something.

97
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:40,600
Stop saying nonsense.

98
00:12:42,467 --> 00:12:44,233
Nonsense?

99
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:50,467
You've forgotten your place, Tae Jeong.

100
00:12:50,467 --> 00:12:53,233
Sorry, I'm sorry.

101
00:12:54,700 --> 00:12:57,300
You crybaby.

102
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,967
Oh, dear.

103
00:13:05,167 --> 00:13:07,167
This is really comfy, huh?

104
00:13:07,167 --> 00:13:09,733
Nice place you got, eh?

105
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:13,067
Anyone might believe
that your family is still rich.

106
00:13:17,467 --> 00:13:19,967
Come on now, show me the text.

107
00:13:19,967 --> 00:13:23,000
Huh? Yeah.

108
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:35,300
I'm worried, too,
but looks like he's doing well.

109
00:13:37,033 --> 00:13:39,100
Hey, you punk.

110
00:13:39,100 --> 00:13:43,067
He told you to beat it.
Why did you crawl back in here?

111
00:13:44,067 --> 00:13:49,000
Well... my funds are a bit tight lately.

112
00:13:50,933 --> 00:13:54,976
You pathetic loser.
You should've tried saving up.

113
00:13:54,976 --> 00:13:57,267
Darn it!

114
00:13:57,267 --> 00:14:01,600
Why didn't that punk say where he was going?

115
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:03,767
I should get going.

116
00:14:17,233 --> 00:14:19,167
Is this yours?

117
00:14:20,467 --> 00:14:23,300
Huh? Yeah.

118
00:14:23,300 --> 00:14:25,100
Nice.

119
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:27,233
Give this to me.

120
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:28,967
Huh?

121
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:33,833
I was just kidding, man.

122
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:43,567
If you hear from Dong Hwa, let me know.

123
00:14:43,567 --> 00:14:45,767
Don't go off on your own.

124
00:14:45,767 --> 00:14:47,033
When did I do that?

125
00:14:47,033 --> 00:14:51,767
You idiot.
You miss evidence right in front of you.

126
00:14:51,767 --> 00:14:53,100
What?

127
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:56,267
I'm leaving. See you later.

128
00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,667
I'll go wash up.

129
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:47,067
Aren't you hungry?

130
00:15:47,067 --> 00:15:48,967
Not in the mood.

131
00:15:51,667 --> 00:15:54,267
Your stomach seems to be.

132
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:03,267
The eggs look a little burnt?

133
00:16:04,233 --> 00:16:05,267
I know.

134
00:16:05,267 --> 00:16:07,967
How could you mess up frying eggs?

135
00:16:10,067 --> 00:16:13,300
It's the pan. It doesn't work.

136
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:18,467
- If you don't like it--
- It's okay. I'll eat it.

137
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:31,167
What?

138
00:16:31,167 --> 00:16:35,167
Why did you hide me?

139
00:16:35,167 --> 00:16:37,500
I wasn't hiding you.

140
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,200
You're lying.

141
00:16:40,600 --> 00:16:42,700
You saw me.

142
00:16:46,367 --> 00:16:49,067
Sorry for deceiving you.

143
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:52,200
As soon as I find proof,

144
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:54,533
I'll get out of here.

145
00:16:54,533 --> 00:16:56,967
Do it in two days.

146
00:16:56,967 --> 00:16:59,733
I'll need to leave too by then.

147
00:16:59,733 --> 00:17:02,400
- Thanks.
- Hold on.

148
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:06,800
You probably misunderstood Dong Hwa.

149
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:10,500
He's a good person.

150
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:11,933
How can you be so sure?

151
00:17:11,933 --> 00:17:13,833
I know him.

152
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:16,200
He's my closest friend.

153
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:22,833
But what kind of proof are you looking for?

154
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:28,600
Heo Dong Hwa has a secret phone.

155
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:32,933
A phone shouldn't be that hard to find.

156
00:17:34,667 --> 00:17:37,267
But it hasn't turned up yet.

157
00:17:37,267 --> 00:17:40,333
Must be hidden real well.

158
00:17:40,333 --> 00:17:42,700
This house is like a maze.

159
00:17:42,700 --> 00:17:45,200
Lots of hiding spots too.

160
00:17:46,467 --> 00:17:48,667
I'll help you look for it.

161
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:51,533
No need.

162
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:54,600
It's my job.

163
00:17:54,600 --> 00:17:57,000
You need to find your family, right?

164
00:18:23,067 --> 00:18:25,100
Dong Hwa's passport?

165
00:18:25,100 --> 00:18:28,767
So he was lying that he's abroad.

166
00:18:30,200 --> 00:18:31,933
No way...

167
00:18:43,567 --> 00:18:46,533
Did he text me here,
pretending to be Dong Hwa?

168
00:18:58,700 --> 00:19:00,933
[Tae Jeong, I just saw your text
because I'm abroad.]

169
00:19:00,933 --> 00:19:04,500
Why bother impersonating Dong Hwa?

170
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:09,167
Where did you go?

171
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:11,400
I had some quick errands to run.

172
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:13,367
Is something wrong?

173
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,967
What's that sound?

174
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:25,033
It sounds like it's coming
from outside, right?

175
00:19:25,033 --> 00:19:27,333
I need to go take care of something.

176
00:19:27,333 --> 00:19:29,033
Get some rest.

177
00:19:31,533 --> 00:19:34,100
What is he trying to hide?

178
00:19:36,992 --> 00:19:40,766
Why did he tell me to stay away,
pretending that Dong Hwa had gone abroad?

179
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:46,767
If he's just looking for a phone,
why go this far?

180
00:19:48,867 --> 00:19:52,833
What if there's a bigger secret
I shouldn't be here for?

181
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:56,767
No way...
